## What To Keep In Mind

The short version is:

JIT code is not only about arithmetic or branches.

It must cooperate with object lifetime.

If you remember only one rule from this chapter, let it be this:

Never let the GC lose track of a live pointer.

The next chapter explains another major runtime bridge: native builtins.
